SIMPLE: oviduct
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oviduct
<hw>O"vi*duct</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Ov</ets>um +
<ets>duct</ets>: cf. F. <ets>oviducte</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>A tube, or duct, for the passage of ova from the ovary to the
exterior of the animal or to the part where further development takes
place. In mammals the oviducts are also called <altname>Fallopian
tubes</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oviferous</ent>⟦br⟧
